parameters.name: model_id
parameters.label: model_id
parameters.help: Destination id for this model; auto-generated if not specified.

parameters.name: training_frame
parameters.label: training_frame
parameters.help: Id of the training data frame.

parameters.name: validation_frame
parameters.label: validation_frame
parameters.help: Id of the validation data frame.

parameters.name: nfolds
parameters.label: nfolds
parameters.help: Number of folds for K-fold cross-validation (0 to disable or >= 2).

parameters.name: checkpoint
parameters.label: checkpoint
parameters.help: Model checkpoint to resume training with.

parameters.name: export_checkpoints_dir
parameters.label: export_checkpoints_dir
parameters.help: Automatically export generated models to this directory.

parameters.name: seed
parameters.label: seed
parameters.help: Seed for pseudo random number generator (if applicable).

parameters.name: keep_cross_validation_models
parameters.label: keep_cross_validation_models
parameters.help: Whether to keep the cross-validation models.

parameters.name: keep_cross_validation_predictions
parameters.label: keep_cross_validation_predictions
parameters.help: Whether to keep the predictions of the cross-validation models.

parameters.name: keep_cross_validation_fold_assignment
parameters.label: keep_cross_validation_fold_assignment
parameters.help: Whether to keep the cross-validation fold assignment.

parameters.name: fold_assignment
parameters.label: fold_assignment
parameters.help: Cross-validation fold assignment scheme, if fold_column is not specified. The 'Stratified' option will stratify the folds based on the response variable, for classification problems.

parameters.name: fold_column
parameters.label: fold_column
parameters.help: Column with cross-validation fold index assignment per observation.

parameters.name: response_column
parameters.label: response_column
parameters.help: Response variable column.

parameters.name: ignored_columns
parameters.label: ignored_columns
parameters.help: Names of columns to ignore for training.

parameters.name: ignore_const_cols
parameters.label: ignore_const_cols
parameters.help: Ignore constant columns.

parameters.name: score_each_iteration
parameters.label: score_each_iteration
parameters.help: Whether to score during each iteration of model training.

parameters.name: score_iteration_interval
parameters.label: score_iteration_interval
parameters.help: Perform scoring for every score_iteration_interval iterations.

parameters.name: offset_column
parameters.label: offset_column
parameters.help: Offset column. This will be added to the combination of columns before applying the link function.

parameters.name: weights_column
parameters.label: weights_column
parameters.help: Column with observation weights. Giving some observation a weight of zero is equivalent to excluding it from the dataset; giving an observation a relative weight of 2 is equivalent to repeating that row twice. Negative weights are not allowed. Note: Weights are per-row observation weights and do not increase the size of the data frame. This is typically the number of times a row is repeated, but non-integer values are supported as well. During training, rows with higher weights matter more, due to the larger loss function pre-factor. If you set weight = 0 for a row, the returned prediction frame at that row is zero and this is incorrect. To get an accurate prediction, remove all rows with weight == 0.

parameters.name: family
parameters.label: family
parameters.help: Family. Use binomial for classification with logistic regression, others are for regression problems.

parameters.name: tweedie_variance_power
parameters.label: tweedie_variance_power
parameters.help: Tweedie variance power

parameters.name: tweedie_link_power
parameters.label: tweedie_link_power
parameters.help: Tweedie link power.

parameters.name: theta
parameters.label: theta
parameters.help: Theta

parameters.name: solver
parameters.label: solver
parameters.help: AUTO will set the solver based on given data and the other parameters. IRLSM is fast on on problems with small number of predictors and for lambda-search with L1 penalty, L_BFGS scales better for datasets with many columns.

parameters.name: alpha
parameters.label: alpha
parameters.help: Distribution of regularization between the L1 (Lasso) and L2 (Ridge) penalties. A value of 1 for alpha represents Lasso regression, a value of 0 produces Ridge regression, and anything in between specifies the amount of mixing between the two. Default value of alpha is 0 when SOLVER = 'L-BFGS'; 0.5 otherwise.

parameters.name: lambda
parameters.label: lambda
parameters.help: Regularization strength

parameters.name: lambda_search
parameters.label: lambda_search
parameters.help: Use lambda search starting at lambda max, given lambda is then interpreted as lambda min.

parameters.name: early_stopping
parameters.label: early_stopping
parameters.help: Stop early when there is no more relative improvement on train or validation (if provided).

parameters.name: nlambdas
parameters.label: nlambdas
parameters.help: Number of lambdas to be used in a search. Default indicates: If alpha is zero, with lambda search set to True, the value of nlamdas is set to 30 (fewer lambdas are needed for ridge regression) otherwise it is set to 100.

parameters.name: standardize
parameters.label: standardize
parameters.help: Standardize numeric columns to have zero mean and unit variance.

parameters.name: missing_values_handling
parameters.label: missing_values_handling
parameters.help: Handling of missing values. Either MeanImputation, Skip or PlugValues.

parameters.name: plug_values
parameters.label: plug_values
parameters.help: Plug Values (a single row frame containing values that will be used to impute missing values of the training/validation frame, use with conjunction missing_values_handling = PlugValues).

parameters.name: compute_p_values
parameters.label: compute_p_values
parameters.help: Request p-values computation, p-values work only with IRLSM solver.

parameters.name: dispersion_parameter_method
parameters.label: dispersion_parameter_method
parameters.help: Method used to estimate the dispersion parameter for Tweedie, Gamma and Negative Binomial only.

parameters.name: init_dispersion_parameter
parameters.label: init_dispersion_parameter
parameters.help: Only used for Tweedie, Gamma and Negative Binomial GLM.  Store the initial value of dispersion parameter.  If fix_dispersion_parameter is set, this value will be used in the calculation of p-values.

parameters.name: remove_collinear_columns
parameters.label: remove_collinear_columns
parameters.help: In case of linearly dependent columns, remove the dependent columns.

parameters.name: intercept
parameters.label: intercept
parameters.help: Include constant term in the model

parameters.name: non_negative
parameters.label: non_negative
parameters.help: Restrict coefficients (not intercept) to be non-negative.

parameters.name: max_iterations
parameters.label: max_iterations
parameters.help: Maximum number of iterations.  Value should >=1.  A value of 0 is only set when only the model coefficient names and model coefficient dimensions are needed.

parameters.name: objective_epsilon
parameters.label: objective_epsilon
parameters.help: Converge if  objective value changes less than this. Default (of -1.0) indicates: If lambda_search is set to True the value of objective_epsilon is set to .0001. If the lambda_search is set to False and lambda is equal to zero, the value of objective_epsilon is set to .000001, for any other value of lambda the default value of objective_epsilon is set to .0001.

parameters.name: beta_epsilon
parameters.label: beta_epsilon
parameters.help: Converge if beta changes less (using L-infinity norm) than beta esilon. ONLY applies to IRLSM solver.

parameters.name: gradient_epsilon
parameters.label: gradient_epsilon
parameters.help: Converge if  objective changes less (using L-infinity norm) than this, ONLY applies to L-BFGS solver. Default (of -1.0) indicates: If lambda_search is set to False and lambda is equal to zero, the default value of gradient_epsilon is equal to .000001, otherwise the default value is .0001. If lambda_search is set to True, the conditional values above are 1E-8 and 1E-6 respectively.

parameters.name: link
parameters.label: link
parameters.help: Link function.

parameters.name: startval
parameters.label: startval
parameters.help: double array to initialize coefficients for GLM.  If standardize is true, the standardized coefficients should be used.  Otherwise, use the regular coefficients.

parameters.name: calc_like
parameters.label: calc_like
parameters.help: if true, will return likelihood function value.

parameters.name: prior
parameters.label: prior
parameters.help: Prior probability for y==1. To be used only for logistic regression iff the data has been sampled and the mean of response does not reflect reality.

parameters.name: cold_start
parameters.label: cold_start
parameters.help: Only applicable to multiple alpha/lambda values.  If false, build the next model for next set of alpha/lambda values starting from the values provided by current model.  If true will start GLM model from scratch.

parameters.name: lambda_min_ratio
parameters.label: lambda_min_ratio
parameters.help: Minimum lambda used in lambda search, specified as a ratio of lambda_max (the smallest lambda that drives all coefficients to zero).  Default indicates: if the number of observations is greater than the number of variables, then lambda_min_ratio is set to 0.0001; if the number of observations is less than the number of variables, then lambda_min_ratio is set to 0.01.

parameters.name: beta_constraints
parameters.label: beta_constraints
parameters.help: Beta constraints

parameters.name: max_active_predictors
parameters.label: max_active_predictors
parameters.help: Maximum number of active predictors during computation. Use as a stopping criterion to prevent expensive model building with many predictors. Default indicates: If the IRLSM solver is used, the value of max_active_predictors is set to 5000 otherwise it is set to 100000000.

parameters.name: interactions
parameters.label: interactions
parameters.help: A list of predictor column indices to interact. All pairwise combinations will be computed for the list.

parameters.name: interaction_pairs
parameters.label: interaction_pairs
parameters.help: A list of pairwise (first order) column interactions.

parameters.name: obj_reg
parameters.label: obj_reg
parameters.help: Likelihood divider in objective value computation, default (of -1.0) will set it to 1/nobs.

parameters.name: stopping_rounds
parameters.label: stopping_rounds
parameters.help: Early stopping based on convergence of stopping_metric. Stop if simple moving average of length k of the stopping_metric does not improve for k:=stopping_rounds scoring events (0 to disable)

parameters.name: stopping_metric
parameters.label: stopping_metric
parameters.help: Metric to use for early stopping (AUTO: logloss for classification, deviance for regression and anomaly_score for Isolation Forest). Note that custom and custom_increasing can only be used in GBM and DRF with the Python client.

parameters.name: stopping_tolerance
parameters.label: stopping_tolerance
parameters.help: Relative tolerance for metric-based stopping criterion (stop if relative improvement is not at least this much)

parameters.name: balance_classes
parameters.label: balance_classes
parameters.help: Balance training data class counts via over/under-sampling (for imbalanced data).

parameters.name: class_sampling_factors
parameters.label: class_sampling_factors
parameters.help: Desired over/under-sampling ratios per class (in lexicographic order). If not specified, sampling factors will be automatically computed to obtain class balance during training. Requires balance_classes.

parameters.name: max_after_balance_size
parameters.label: max_after_balance_size
parameters.help: Maximum relative size of the training data after balancing class counts (can be less than 1.0). Requires balance_classes.

parameters.name: max_confusion_matrix_size
parameters.label: max_confusion_matrix_size
parameters.help: [Deprecated] Maximum size (# classes) for confusion matrices to be printed in the Logs.

parameters.name: max_runtime_secs
parameters.label: max_runtime_secs
parameters.help: Maximum allowed runtime in seconds for model training. Use 0 to disable.

parameters.name: custom_metric_func
parameters.label: custom_metric_func
parameters.help: Reference to custom evaluation function, format: `language:keyName=funcName`

parameters.name: generate_scoring_history
parameters.label: generate_scoring_history
parameters.help: If set to true, will generate scoring history for GLM.  This may significantly slow down the algo.

parameters.name: auc_type
parameters.label: auc_type
parameters.help: Set default multinomial AUC type.

parameters.name: dispersion_epsilon
parameters.label: dispersion_epsilon
parameters.help: If changes in dispersion parameter estimation or loglikelihood value is smaller than dispersion_epsilon, will break out of the dispersion parameter estimation loop using maximum likelihood.

parameters.name: tweedie_epsilon
parameters.label: tweedie_epsilon
parameters.help: In estimating tweedie dispersion parameter using maximum likelihood, this is used to choose the lower and upper indices in the approximating of the infinite series summation.

parameters.name: max_iterations_dispersion
parameters.label: max_iterations_dispersion
parameters.help: Control the maximum number of iterations in the dispersion parameter estimation loop using maximum likelihood.

parameters.name: build_null_model
parameters.label: build_null_model
parameters.help: If set, will build a model with only the intercept.  Default to false.

parameters.name: fix_dispersion_parameter
parameters.label: fix_dispersion_parameter
parameters.help: Only used for Tweedie, Gamma and Negative Binomial GLM.  If set, will use the dispsersion parameter in init_dispersion_parameter as the standard error and use it to calculate the p-values. Default to false.

parameters.name: generate_variable_inflation_factors
parameters.label: generate_variable_inflation_factors
parameters.help: if true, will generate variable inflation factors for numerical predictors.  Default to false.

parameters.name: fix_tweedie_variance_power
parameters.label: fix_tweedie_variance_power
parameters.help: If true, will fix tweedie variance power value to the value set in tweedie_variance_power.

parameters.name: dispersion_learning_rate
parameters.label: dispersion_learning_rate
parameters.help: Dispersion learning rate is only valid for tweedie family dispersion parameter estimation using ml. It must be > 0.  This controls how much the dispersion parameter estimate is to be changed when the calculated loglikelihood actually decreases with the new dispersion.  In this case, instead of setting new dispersion = dispersion + change, we set new dispersion = dispersion + dispersion_learning_rate * change. Defaults to 0.5.

parameters.name: influence
parameters.label: influence
parameters.help: If set to dfbetas will calculate the difference in beta when a datarow is included and excluded in the dataset.

parameters.name: gainslift_bins
parameters.label: gainslift_bins
parameters.help: Gains/Lift table number of bins. 0 means disabled.. Default value -1 means automatic binning.

parameters.name: linear_constraints
parameters.label: linear_constraints
parameters.help: Linear constraints: used to specify linear constraints involving more than one coefficients in standard form.  It is only supported for solver IRLSM.  It contains four columns: names (strings for coefficient names or constant), values, types ( strings of 'Equal' or 'LessThanEqual'), constraint_numbers (0 for first linear constraint, 1 for second linear constraint, ...).

parameters.name: init_optimal_glm
parameters.label: init_optimal_glm
parameters.help: If true, will initialize coefficients with values derived from GLM runs without linear constraints.  Only available for linear constraints.

parameters.name: separate_linear_beta
parameters.label: separate_linear_beta
parameters.help: If true, will keep the beta constraints and linear constraints separate.  After new coefficients are found, first beta constraints will be applied followed by the application of linear constraints.  Note that the beta constraints in this case will not be part of the objective function.  If false, will combine the beta and linear constraints.

parameters.name: constraint_eta0
parameters.label: constraint_eta0
parameters.help: For constrained GLM only.  It affects the setting of eta_k+1=eta_0/power(ck+1, alpha).

parameters.name: constraint_tau
parameters.label: constraint_tau
parameters.help: For constrained GLM only.  It affects the setting of c_k+1=tau*c_k.

parameters.name: constraint_alpha
parameters.label: constraint_alpha
parameters.help: For constrained GLM only.  It affects the setting of  eta_k = eta_0/pow(c_0, alpha).

parameters.name: constraint_beta
parameters.label: constraint_beta
parameters.help: For constrained GLM only.  It affects the setting of eta_k+1 = eta_k/pow(c_k, beta).

parameters.name: constraint_c0
parameters.label: constraint_c0
parameters.help: For constrained GLM only.  It affects the initial setting of epsilon_k = 1/c_0.

data: Mojo 2 pipeline extensions, Amazon S3, Algos, Infogram, AutoML, Core V3, TargetEncoder, Core V4

help.__meta: Metadata on this schema instance, to make it self-describing.
help.cross_validation_predictions: Cross-validation predictions, one per cv model (deprecated, use cross_validation_holdout_predictions_frame_id instead)
help.lambda_best: Lambda minimizing the objective value, only applicable with lambda search or when arrays of alpha and lambdas are provided
help.linear_constraints_table: Table of beta (if exists) and linear constraints values and status
help.all_constraints_satisfied: True if all constraints conditions are satisfied.  Otherwise, false.
help.cross_validation_fold_assignment_frame_i: Cross-validation fold assignment (each row is assigned to one holdout fold)
help.regression_influence_diagnostics: Contains the original dataset and the dfbetas calculated for each predictor.
help.lambda_1se: Lambda best + 1 standard error. Only applicable with lambda search and cross-validation
help.vif_predictor_names: Predictor names where variable inflation factors are calculated.
help.lambda_max: Starting lambda value used when lambda search is enabled.
help.linear_constraint_states: Beta (if exists) and linear constraints states
help.dispersion: Dispersion parameter, only applicable to Tweedie family (input/output) and fractional Binomial (output only)
help.cross_validation_holdout_predictions_fra: Cross-validation holdout predictions (full out-of-sample predictions on training data)
help.alpha_best: Alpha minimizing the objective value, only applicable when arrays of alphas are given
help.lambda_min: Minimum lambda value calculated that may be used for lambda search.  Early-stop may happen and the minimum lambda value will not be used in this case.
help.coefficients_table_multinomials_with_cla: Table of Coefficients with coefficients denoted with class names for GLM multinonimals only.
help.best_submodel_index: submodel index minimizing the objective value, only applicable for arrays of alphas/lambda
